The '''R-46''' was an [[intercontinental ballistic missile]] (ICBM) design by the [[Soviet Union]] during the [[Cold War]].

The R-46 concept was to launch a very large [[hydrogen bomb]] into orbit as a [[Fractional Orbital Bombardment System|fractional orbital bombardment system]] (FOBS).  The existence of the system was alluded to in a speech by then [[Soviet Premier]] [[Nikita Khrushchev]] in 1961.  The design was not developed, however, and the FOBS concept was abandoned as part of [[SALT II]].

