The '''rapid anti-personnel minefield breaching system''' or '''RAMBS II''' is a British [[rifle grenade]] used to breach obstacles and clear [[minefield]]s. It is designed to replace the [[Bangalore torpedo]], offering a more effective and flexible alternative. When deployed, the RAMBS II will clear a path 60 metres long and 0.6 metres wide, compared to the Bangalore's cleared area that is 15 metres long and 1 metre wide.

